messages.content: It‚Äôs a ballroom. She‚Äôs only been here once or twice before, but she waltzes in like nothing could be more natural.

author.name: scipe

messages.content: She‚Äôs not wearing the standard outfit people who have met her before or seen a depiction of her for whatever reason would recognize; the pajama-like dress and out-of-place headphones obscuring a black hair bow. Instead, she‚Äôs wearing something in between a suit and a dress, something pure white, like a mannequin. She holds within her hands a baton.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: She bows, hand in front of her chest.

author.name: scipe

messages.content: ‚ÄúHello, everyone.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content:
She returns to standing up straight.
‚ÄúMy name is Eulogia Praxis.‚Äù
She‚Äôs standing proud and tall. She‚Äôs clearly the same girl, but none of the vaguely sickly feeling behavior of the old Eulogia remains.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúI understand some of you might be confused and scared. I‚Äôm sorry about that. Both the parts I do and don‚Äôt know about.‚Äù She frowns.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Eulogia quickly returns to a pleasant smile, however. She‚Äôs doing her best, recalling all the dictation her mother provided on manners before giving up on integrating her into society.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúIn summary, the rest of the royal family have become unfit to serve. Death, unknown whereabouts, physical absence, and problems of temperament have made all of them either unable to take the role of a monarch, or harmful when doing so. I will accept this burden on their behalf.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúI believe my father‚Äôs greatest mistake was his inaction. More than any outright cruelty, he simply ignored much of the suffering of the people he should have been caring for.‚Äù Eulogia is still smiling, but her eyes look to the side, obviously less pleased to talk about this part.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúThis isn‚Äôt a result of any ill intent. I truly believe that. Think I‚Äôm biased if you will. But I cannot deny it was a mistake. I will be a much more‚Ä¶ active ruler!‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: She puts a finger to her chin. ‚ÄúI haven‚Äôt decided on a title, actually‚Ä¶ I can‚Äôt be the king, so would that make me queen? That feels odd. I suppose there‚Äôs some time to decide. I don‚Äôt mind if anyone just calls me Eulogia, anyway! Just happy to talk.‚Äù She closes her eyes with a wide grin saying this, then opens them again. There‚Äôs a far-away stare to them.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúI know it‚Äôs scary. When things change. I think everyone feels like that in their own way. But I am more than my father or mother. Far from ignoring systemic issues I could be making policies related to, I am much more tangibly capable of improving people‚Äôs lives in many ways, and it would be improper of me to not attempt to.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: She slams the baton down into her open palm a few times, as an idle action. ‚ÄúI am a powerful user of magic! I will bring Arctica into a new world of peace and love. No one will have to be alone or in pain. I just need to figure a few things out first. Excuse the rocky transitionary period.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúPlease look forward to it!‚Äù She waves.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: No one would ever be able to quite explain how it happened, or easily verbalize the experience. But upon the moment in time at this location when ‚ÄòChapter 16‚Äô of The Antarctica Project began, everyone within a certain radius of the royal palace, large enough to include the entire capital, would witness this scene.

messages.content: None of Solnit, Eulogia Praxis, or Virtos Dextrum are in this room anymore. But Baby Crippler is.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: **MBMJ crosses his arms.** "How'd you find your way into the palace? Here to execute me, to take revenge? For Arctica, crippler?"

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúMy CELL. It was UNLOCKED. I do not know what drew me here specifically‚Ä¶ but I am here, now.‚Äù He crosses his arms in turn. ‚ÄúIt has been some time, Man. And yet not much at all.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "A cell opened, hmm? Well then. I believe you have been afforded a pardon- a royal pardon, in fact. There was a reshuffling of authority. An ongoing blip, after thr ptrhioud entourage... ahem..." **MBMJ shakes his head.** "...I'm sorry for your loss."

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content: "Elithabeza... I mean."

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúAh. I SEE. She did not make it, then.‚Äù Baby Crippler stares down at the ground. ‚ÄúAnnice, I shouldn‚Äôt be here. That‚Ä¶ that was supposed to be my last STAND. The END of Baby Crippler, and any other names such a bag of bones might have gone by. I have not prepared to LIVE with the consequences of my actions.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: **MBMJ grins at Baby Crippler.** "And yet  among all those destiny would choose to bestow their gifts on, they choose you. Will you refuse this fate, friend turned rival, and wish to be rendered to dust, or will you venture forth, and seek further enlightenment?"

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content: He gives a short, gruff laugh. ‚ÄúHah. That is the karmic WHEEL we are saddled with, I suppose‚Ä¶ the END of one arc will always beget another BEGINNING.‚Äù He extends a hand. ‚ÄúI do not particularly WANT to fight you. At the moment, I merely wish to understand what the FUCK is going on.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: **MBMJ grasps BC's hand, and gives it a firm shake.** "I believe this is somewhat of a convergence, friend. There is a scene somewhere awaiting our debut."

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúThey‚Ä¶ they knew what they were getting into! But NO, I‚Äôm uncertain how many managed to make it out.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: There are no people immediately visible outside. The entire place looks‚Ä¶ unusual, somehow. Like a recreation of a recreation of the actual building. It‚Äôs vague enough to seem like you might just be seeing things, though.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Wyrd came after some of them. You have made some unique enemies, friend."

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúWyrd‚Ä¶‚Äù He mutters. ‚ÄúI‚Äôve never met the man, but I‚Äôve heard ENOUGH. These are strange times‚Ä¶‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "...Hm." **MBMJ casts detect magic again.** "It seems we are still in some sort of abstraction."

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content:
Yeah, there‚Äôs magic up the wazoo. Enough to make the spell hard to use practically. It does seem to ebb and flow in different concentrations. It‚Äôs most immediately concentrated nearby around you and BC.

‚ÄúPeculiar. I am afraid I‚Äôm a novice at magical matters not associated with LIMB MOBILITY.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Cast into yet another world of fancy and intrigue. I feel as if someone is attempting to teach me a lesson- a lesson I am stubbornly refusing to learn."

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúIt becomes harder to learn the more you grow, the more you become set in your ways. I cannot even glean what could qualify as a ‚Äòlesson‚Äô here.‚Äù BC.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Yes... I have no idea why you've been pulled into this illusion with me. I seem to keep pulling people into these... alternate realms of existence."

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content: "It feels... substantial. I know it MUST be an illusion by sight, but it does not feel like one. ODD."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "...So funny, being in this kind of space. Been told so many times that you can just dispel it with your mind. By deciding it so, you can turn illusions into mist. And yet the true illusions, the reflections of what is purely unnatural and broken in the world, those are the illusions that repel dispelling."

‚ÄúThis labyrinth of memories‚Ä¶ is killing me.‚Äù Baby Crippler whispers somberly.

messages.content: He turns around. He‚Äôs messing with some bit of electronics. ‚ÄúOh. It‚Äôs been some time. Hello.‚Äù He tips his fedora.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "We haven't met for a while! Hows the criminal business doing?"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúFine. But I prefer ‚Äòmercenary‚Äô. On a pretty big job right now.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Are you at any right to explain?"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content:
‚ÄúI dunno.‚Äù He turns to Neko. ‚ÄúIs he with us?‚Äù

She shrugs laboriously. ‚ÄúHell if I know. I hope.‚Äù

Isador is quiet for a second, then mutters incoherently before speaking. ‚ÄúWell, I‚Äôm setting up a bomb, for one.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Bombs are nice!"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: "Have no worries, Isador!!! I should be more scared of you than you of me!!!"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

attachments.url: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\wideGrin-7B4C3.png

messages.content: "Your secret is safe."

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: "Well, it won't be secret soon. This time is our advantage. They're gonna be on our asses the second we have our way in. Ageny, make yourself useful and round everybody up." Skelt sighs and gets to work.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: I turn to Neko. "What do you mean by traditionalism?"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: "It's what I've parsed from you. You reject your parents by clinging to a name associated with ancestry further back. You rebel against society nominally, but possess a distaste for the concept of rebellion." Neko replies.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "I see."

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: "Am I... am I any good at it?"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content:
"What? I don't know how someone could be 'good' at something like that. It's just a description of a pattern. That's a way you've operated. At times, at least. I don't think you're devoutly committed to it. It's just... an observation. Of how you orient yourself around the world you find yourself in."
Neko takes off her sunglasses.
"...But this world hasn't done a damn thing for you. It's taken everything at every turn. It's given you nothing but a pretense of freedom. I don't think a single person on it cares about you at all."
She hugs Intuition and whispers. "Except me."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: *No... is this some kind of lotus eating machine?!!!! Is X trying to spite me?!! No. No. I've won. I've won. I found the coding. I've found the trick. I have to preserve it. I have to preserve it.*

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: "You're right.... Horatius.... Mom..... they didn't mean anything!!! We barely even talk!!!! You were.... you were everything they were supposed to be!"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

attachments.url: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\sadSmile-B2DBC.png

messages.content: She holds that for a few seconds, and then pulls back. ‚ÄúYou‚Äôre a good kid at heart. I‚Äôm sorry nobody else sees that. I can‚Äôt answer every question about who you are and why. But I‚Äôm here if you need me. To talk, or whatever. ‚Ä¶So right now, please be here for me.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: "So whats with the bomb?"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content:
Skelt shows up with a group gathered just in time to witness the end of that interaction and probably silently be weird about that.

Neko speaks up, loud enough for anyone else in the group still clueless to hear. ‚ÄúThis building is in an absurdly convenient‚Ä¶ or inconvenient, depending on perspective, location. It‚Äôs not too far, spatially, from our goal. We‚Äôre gonna make a tunnel long enough to connect to an underground prison. ‚Ä¶You know the one, Intuition. From there, we‚Äôll rendezvous with our allies on the other end.‚Äù 
She sighs. ‚ÄúCompletely unrelated‚Ä¶ The group known as the *Gadflies* has abandoned us to do‚Ä¶ whatever they‚Äôre going to do. The hope is that we can make as much of a dent as possible on the divided attention of the guard to render them easy pickings. Even though he barely fuckin‚Äô coordinated with me at all‚Ä¶‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Gadflies... how much did I miss when I was gone?"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content:
‚ÄúThey‚Äôre the people who hang around Wress. I think he‚Äôs separately arranged some nonsense where the attention of the government as a whole will be divided by what more local authorities he could recruit to the cause, so he‚Äôs not entirely useless. ‚Ä¶Though I have no idea how relevant that is now. This whole city is‚Ä¶ isolated, for the moment, I think.‚Äù
She clears her throat. ‚ÄúThere‚Äôs some things I should explain. There‚Äôs gonna be at most like, fifty people total in the palace right now. Discounting reinforcements called. Twenty in the guard. A dozen or so servants who happen to be on call. And that leaves a bunch of vaguely significant assholes I‚Äôll try to iterate through if it becomes necessary. Most imminently‚Ä¶ Eulogia. I don‚Äôt know what the fuck she‚Äôs doing. But obviously, there‚Äôs a risk she‚Äôll end up interfering. If you see her, don‚Äôt engage with her unless absolutely necessary. If you have to engage with her, remember that we‚Äôre not in the business of child murder.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Eulogia saved my life! I would never kill her."

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content:
‚ÄúGood.‚Äù She doesn‚Äôt actually understand what this is referring to, but that‚Äôs fine.
‚ÄúOur goal is the surrender‚Ä¶ or complete incapacitation‚Ä¶ of the monarch.‚Äù
She sighs, then purses her lips. ‚ÄúThat would likely make our final destination the study past the throne room.‚Äù
She puts her sunglasses back on and makes some sort of signal to Skelt, who nods.
‚ÄúEveryone clear? We‚Äôre hoping we‚Äôll end up with the easier path in, but be ready for anything.‚Äù
The crowd vaguely murmurs.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Intuition kind of just silently follows.

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: I try to interact with Skelt.

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content:
"Isador. Do it."

Isador activates whatever device he was messing with and steps back. It burrows into the wall for some time.

Skelt shushes the approaching Intuition Overdrive.

Neko clears her throat, clearly expecting something to have happened sooner. "No idea who the old man's wrangled up in his support, if anyone... I just hope I don't have to explain shit again..."

A loud explosion occurs. The smoke clears, and there's a large hole through what was once solid ground. It doesn't collapse in on itself, and Isador silently does a victorious fist pump.

It doesn't seem to lead anywhere but a dead end, though.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Intuition investigates the dead end.

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: Neko heads in as well. It does seem to lead nowhere. ‚ÄúAny second now.‚Äù She mutters.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Was it intended to be like this?"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: Intuition tries to look closer.

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content:
‚ÄúYes‚Ä¶ we need to make sure it meets the other end. So‚Äî‚Äù
As other people begin following suit, the dead end bursts open, creating the complete tunnel as planned. On the other side is the prison he once inhabited with the likes of Hirer Dreng and Joe Biden. Visible immediately are five people, of which Intuition would recognize two: Erica Furuda and Virtos Dextrum. He probably also is capable of identifying the blue-and-yellow suited wrestler, however.

((End session.))

She blinks.

"What? Huh? What?"

After going through her usual morning routine, she wheels out of her quarters. This can't be right.

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content:
Joliene encounters Morsirius in the hall.
‚ÄúOh! Uh, hello‚Ä¶ I think there‚Äôs problems. Just generally‚Ä¶‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "...I guess you could call this a 'general problem', sure. What... what the *fuck* happened?"

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúThe, uh‚Ä¶ princess, I guess? She‚Äôs‚Ä¶ gone rogue. Her Majesty sent me to deal with it. Then she said to find you, because she thought I wasn‚Äôt competent enough to deal with it. She seems real stressed!‚Äù Morsirius shakes his head.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Her Majesty... um. You're referring to Zita, correct?"

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúYeah, her.‚Äù Morsirius clarifies language.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "...Okay. Good. Good... I'll, uh..." She blinks. "Where is she? Her Majesty, I mean."

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúShe was headed to the throne room, I think? She delegated rounding up the rest of the guard still around to the first person besides me who happened to be there, so they could convene strategy or somesuch.‚Äù Morsirius puts a hand to his chin. ‚ÄúOh, right. It was Detlef. Not just some guy. Detlef exists. He‚Äôs the one going and doing that. Detlef Praxis. He exists. I forget that pretty often, surprisingly.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content:
"Detlef exists? I kind of assumed that was already... dealt with, or s- something. W- whatever. I'll just-" She gestures in the direction of the throne room. "Okay. Yeah. Thanks for the information. Bye."

She goes to the throne room.

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content: Joliene encounters Zita just outside the throne room, wearing peculiar armor. She swivels around panicked and draws her weapon, then sighs. ‚ÄúHello, Joliene.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content:
"What the *fuck* is going on?!"

She harshly grabs Zita by the shoulders, leaning forward in her wheelchair.

"That was- that definitely wasn't just me who saw that, right?! How did she do this?! How could you let her-... she can't- she can't get away with this!"

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content:
She shoves Joliene back off her. ‚ÄúI don‚Äôt know. Well, not entirely. I understand some of what‚Äôs going on there. And I *am* worried, of course! But there‚Äôs‚Ä¶ I need to take care of more important matters first. This‚Äîthis couldn‚Äôt have come at a worse time‚Ä¶ she was supposed to be able to stay under control for a while, if that tech, if Dex‚Äî‚Äù
Zita‚Äôs eyes widen. ‚ÄúIt always comes back to him. Dammit. Ovan‚Ä¶ ugh.‚Äù She stares at Joliene. ‚ÄúWas *that* what you came to me to ask?‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "...I- I'm not sure what you mean. I thought you called me. What's this about Dextrum?"

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúI didn‚Äôt‚Ä¶ ugh, did that imbecile screw up the message?!‚Äù She takes a deep breath. ‚ÄúI don‚Äôt trust either of our supposed ‚ÄòAdvisors‚Äô right now.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Please elaborate. Or, uh... I guess Dextrum makes sense. What makes Sinestre any less reliable than usual?"

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúIntruders. From *her* room. There‚Äôs some spatial nonsense, some kind of way in‚Ä¶ and someone used it.‚Äù Zita glances in the direction of the throne room. ‚Äú‚ÄîI, I don‚Äôt have time for this. Do you know where our ballroom is? ‚Ä¶It‚Äôs near the bar.‚Äù She adds this potentially relevant hint after a slight pause.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "...I suppose I've seen it in passing. Is that where Eulogia is?"

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content:
‚ÄúIt should be. Find her. Escort her either to me, or to‚Ä¶‚Äù Zita sighs. ‚ÄúI suppose I *do* have faith in Dextrum regarding this matter specifically. But I don‚Äôt even know where he is. Failing that, if circumstances are such that she won‚Äôt cooperate and you can‚Äôt restrain her‚Ä¶ fine. Come back and report that.‚Äù
She turns back towards the direction of the throne room. ‚ÄúRight now, *I* will deal with *this*.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

‚Äú‚Ä¶This?‚Äù

Joliene tries to peek into the throne room.

messages.content:
Eulogia dodges out of the way. Morsirius, whatever the heck he‚Äôs spent all this time doing, arrives at this room in time to see Joliene attempt to hit a child. 

‚ÄúOh, she is here. Alright.‚Äù Morsirius is here now. He‚Äôs in the room.

Eulogia smiles. ‚ÄúTwo people‚Ä¶?‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: She looks over her shoulder at him. "Do you have any idea what she'd be doing here?"

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content:
‚ÄúPerhaps she intends to host a party. Haha. Not, not really. I doubt that. Just joking. I don‚Äôt really know.‚Äù Morsirius employs some of his trademark humor, a staple aspect of his character.

‚ÄúIt‚Äôs the acoustics. Or maybe the look of the room. It just felt right, at any rate.‚Äù Eulogia.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Were you waiting for someone else? Trying to finalize your coup?" She glares down(?) at the child.

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content:
She‚Äôs a little below eye level, yeah.
‚ÄúI know that word! Coups are violent and unlawful. I won‚Äôt be either. You can‚Äôt call any transfer of power a coup! At any rate‚Ä¶ no, afraid not. I‚Äôm alone right now. Though I probably have a sympathizer of sorts. But no one is coming to perform some violent upheaval in my name. It‚Äôs just little old me.‚Äù She shrugs while smiling with an insufferably smug demeanor.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "...I meant that you put a lot of emphasis on the *you're*. Like you were expecting someone to come babysit you, but it wasn't me." She crosses her arms, giving a huff. "Why don't you listen to your mother? You'll never be fit to lead with this attitude."

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content:
‚ÄúWhy doesn‚Äôt she come here? I‚Äôd love to listen to anything she currently felt interested in saying to me.‚Äù Eulogia, at least one would assume it‚Äôs by her will, levitates tiles on the floor to serve as a staircase, which, in addition to letting her scamper out of reach, feels really antagonistic under the circumstances.

‚ÄúYoung‚Ä¶ uh, miss‚Ä¶ it‚Äôs for your own safety, a lot of things are going on right now, and‚Ä¶‚Äù Morsirius, slowly walking towards her, attempts to negotiate with the child.

‚ÄúI‚Äôm aware, yeah.‚Äù Eulogia rolls her eyes.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Out of spite, she tries to grab one of the tiles and toss it to the ground. "She isn't here because this shouldn't even a problem worth considering. You are *a child*. There's no reason to consider them a threat to the Crown; most of the time, they can hardly control their own emotions."

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content:
Joliene can successfully toss a tile.
‚ÄúI agree. She doesn‚Äôt see me as worth her consideration. I had just hoped to be surprised, I guess. So why am I worth yours, Joliene?‚Äù

‚ÄúI‚Äôm here too‚Ä¶‚Äù Morsirius is wounded.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "My being here is an extension of your mother's consideration. You should know this."

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúIt must be nice to finally have a daughter who listens to her. Ha.‚Äù Though this is definitely mocking in nature, she seems uncomfortably earnest with her next sentence. ‚ÄúIs that a familial position you‚Äôre more comfortable with, then?‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: She knits her brow. *"What?"*

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúWell, like, the whole divorce thing. You have a kid too, right? Even if he never actually shows up. Do you regret him?‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Don't change the subject. None of this has anything to do with him. How would you even... know this?"

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúI read The Antarctica Project. Some of it. Kind of just skimmed what existed. There‚Äôs really way too much to actually understand, especially for how long I had. It was a little while ago. I became the overseer, for whatever reason. You could ask Annice, but I doubt he really gets it any more than I do.‚Äù Eulogia perches on a chandelier.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "...I suppose Dextrum wasn't very careful. But still, this explains nothing. The Project couldn't be further removed from my personal life."

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content:
‚ÄúThat‚Äôs true, but I don‚Äôt really think you‚Äôre understanding me. It was like, if someone wrote, a book. About the stuff that happened to everyone. I dunno.‚Äù Eulogia mutters the end of that.

Morsirius interjects. ‚ÄúSo what exactly is The Antarctica Project?‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "I agree with Morsirius. You're not making sense."

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content:
‚ÄúOh, I thought you knew.‚Äù Morsirius addresses Joliene rather than just the room as a whole.

‚ÄúShe probably knows about as much as me, ultimately.‚Äù Eulogia.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "...I'm not sure how much I should say about The Antarctica Project, honestly. But Eulogia seems to disagree with my definition of it." She looks back to her. Craning her neck up is getting really annoying. "...Are you implying there's a record of my life?"

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúNot the whole thing. Just parts that happened while The Antarctica Project was ongoing.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: *"Wh-"* She's able to stop herself from shouting just in time. "Where is it chronicled? How? Are Dextrum and, uh... Culbasko responsible for this?"

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúCulbasko? Oh, like Erica. I don‚Äôt really know. Probably. The plot is kinda boring, to be totally honest. Just a lot of vague misdirection. I do think Dextrum did something, but what *isn‚Äôt* he involved in, haha.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "That obviously doesn't make sense. Are you saying you just *found* this- this document, The Antarctica Project, laying around? You have to be messing around."

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúNo, it was more like a place. Like some observation area. I remember it being a room that‚Äôs‚Ä¶ whatever a shape with 12 sides is? But also not. It was a little weird and dreamlike, but obviously the information it gave me was true.‚Äù The chandelier she‚Äôs on rotates slowly, and she kicks her feet a little to keep facing the same way.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "...Dodecagon. It's a dodecagon."

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content:
‚ÄúOk, thanks.‚Äù

Morsirius interrupts. ‚ÄúWouldn‚Äôt that be twenty sides? Since a decagon is ten, and it‚Äôs two of that.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content:
Joliene turns back to him for only a moment. "I appreciate the insight."

"...This is ridiculous, I almost don't want to believe you, but I can't come up with any reasonable way you could've known about my marital situation. Even if you're lying about the exact method used, though, you clearly have more information than you should, so... why? Why are you telling me this?"

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúWell, because you asked. But if it‚Äôs about what led you to ask me‚Ä¶ To understand. I want to understand people. It‚Äôs all I can hope to accomplish.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "...Well, then I'll bring it back to the original point. There is nothing for you to understand. I don't know what you intend to accomplish by acting out, but it's not going to work."

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content:
‚ÄúIt already is working, though. Or do you think I and the current situation bear no‚Äî‚Äù 
She stops suddenly, staring down at nowhere in particular.

‚ÄúYeah, probably.‚Äù Morsirius, who barely gets what is happening, musters an answer.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "...Were you just trying to deflect me from the throne room? I can't exactly fight like... this, anyway."

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content:
‚ÄúThe‚Ä¶ throne room? What? Why would you bring that up?! What does that have to do with‚Äî‚Äù
Everyone feels this one. The ground shakes, and a distant muffled noise can be heard.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content: "You're going to explain what you mean by this later. Morsirius, wheel me to the throne room. We need to move quickly."

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content:
‚ÄúW‚Ä¶why‚Ä¶‚Äù 

Eulogia screams, and falls from her perch. The world bends.

((End session))

messages.content: Voreverl reaches the top of the stairs. Behind this door would seem to be the roof of this surprisingly tall complex. DA trails behind, breathing heavily. Your energy is unmatched.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Voreverl reaches a hand out to open the door, but pauses and examines Dawn "...Voreverl Leocot's death match of wits is about to occur. You don't seem to be... much for the physical. I haven't run out of use for you, yet, minion. Stay out of the way if I need to enact my evil judgement on this foolish challenger. Unless I tell you to get in the way, as a last resort."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúYeah, sure. Okay.‚Äù DA leans against the wall.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Voreverl, with her ducks in a row, all ready to march out and raze the lands before her, slams the door open.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Violetta Esposito sits atop a currently inactive AC unit, looking at her phone with earbuds in. She spots Voreverl out of the edge of her vision, and takes the headphones off. She stares silently.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Voreverl quite literally trips over herself upon seeing this, involuntarily having pulled back from her sprint out the door. She pushes away the pain of falling on her ass, and spits out the first thing she can to keep control of the situation "I... I'm stronger now! Don't try anything... I've got magic! I beat up a pirate... a sky pirate! She was really big, too!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúIs that what you‚Äôve been doing?‚Äù She rolls her eyes, and drops down from the AC thing.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "...Yeah!" She stumbles to her feet "Much cooler than whatever you've been up to, which is so irrelevant and unimportant that I haven't heard a thing about it! I would totally make fun of it otherwise, but you're clearly not worth my time."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Violetta drags a large cardboard box out from behind the AC thing. ‚ÄúYeah. Sure. You really haven‚Äôt done much on Earth, hm?‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "That's not true at all! Voreverl Leocot never ceases her endless villainous revolution! I raided a government facility! I became the pope! My Rube Goldberg machine of machinations is going off without a hitch, so prepare to be caught in its jaws!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúWho have you hurt?‚Äù Violetta stares at you.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Voreverl crosses her arms and smirks "No one survives an encounter with Voreverl Leocot unscathed! Not my father, rotting in his little shithole rat den, and certainly not those who distract me from my goals. You'll face your punishment in due time."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúNo, you definitely didn‚Äôt kill him. Sorry to hear the news, by the way.‚Äù She smirks, but it seems incongruent with whatever her eyes are expressing.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "...I got some good licks in. Plus, I may as well have killed him, I left him to be consumed by the rabid dogs of the monarchy. He could only have survived with my supervision. It's like... y'know..." She motions with her hand as she thinks "Like a Bond villain. I left him in my trap! The main villain doesn't dirty her hands with background characters."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúThat‚Äôs good. Good.‚Äù Violetta nods to herself. ‚ÄúThat you think that. Real outstanding gymnastics. This would‚Äôve been pointless if you‚Äôd already gained any sense.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "I have no need for sense... other than the sixth sense, the sense of evil! Gweheh... heh..." She quickly gives up on one of the most forced laughs she's ever given "Just get to the point. You don't call someone to a rooftop to just catch up. Are we dueling, or what?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúSure. Yeah. Sure.‚Äù She steps away from the box, moving closer to the edge of the building. ‚ÄúI always knew you were a rich brat, Jane, but it seems at every turn I find you get coddled even more than I thought.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "What are you even talking about!? I... I disowned my family! My father wanted me dead! I live in a shitty apartment... by choice! The point is they didn't buy me a place to live, or anything, okay!? I'm a self built villain!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúI don‚Äôt really care about how much you want to larp as a commoner.‚Äù Violetta holds up her phone, staring at it. ‚ÄúWhile you were busy being deluded into being a pirate, I followed a trail that honestly? It was probably meant for you. And I solved it. Everything. The whole big mystery behind all this horseshit.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Oh, congrats, you're such a big girl for figuring that out. I had no need to follow a trail set out for me, since Voreverl Leocot breaks the trails! She runs straight through the woods! I know everything about The Antarctica Project! Everything relevant anyway. I've got the hit list of who needs to pay."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúThat‚Äôs nice. But you‚Äôre wrong. There was only one hiccup recently. Otherwise you‚Äôve been following along someone else‚Äôs design perfectly.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Voreverl shrugs "Everyone likes to take credit for how things turn out. Play pretend mastermind, say they had it all planned the whole time. Let's not kid ourselves, Voreverl Leocot is an unpredictable force of chaos! Schrodinger's cat remains within my box! My decisions are unobservable, and poisonous to those who cross me!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
‚ÄúIf you were playing the game fair, I wouldn‚Äôt be the only one pushing back against your nonsense. ‚Ä¶Still, I was taken for a fool myself for a while there.‚Äù
Violetta walks over to you. ‚ÄúDo you have the PDA?‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: She smirks "It's around. Tell me why you want it, and I might let you have a look. We can always do the interrogation the hard way, of course, but wasted time is evil deeds unperformed, so I'd prefer to avoid things getting ugly."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúThere‚Äôs a lot of things I want to tell you so we can settle this feud at last. But I don‚Äôt think you‚Äôll just believe all the things I have to say without proof. So I‚Äôll give it. By showing I really do know things about this project, starting with the secret of that little thing.‚Äù She holds out a hand expectantly. ‚ÄúHave you ever heard of a man named *Rupert Darke*?‚Äù

messages.content: "In that case, don't you think it's clear? The moment one person under you experiences anything negative, by their fault or another's, they will cease to think of you as an effective leader. You have driven away everybody who could ever matter, by ignoring every outcome not favorable to you. You are your father with one extra step, and a failed grandiosity. Don't you see?"

messages.content: "Normalcy is worth guiding others toward, in all of its forms. Now, can we go? Why did this have to be a private conversation? We're wasting time."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "I didn‚Äôt want to force you to out yourself in public, if it was true. Your life would probably have been hard enough already."

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: "And why is that? What about me gives off the impression of hardship?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Well, if you were homosexual. They don‚Äôt live easy lives. That‚Äôs what happens when you‚Äôre singled out for sin by god."

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: "You must be thinking of older times than this. In the modern era, homosexuals are uplifted by society, given unique privilege. To account for their time out of the limelight, I suppose. Anybody would be lucky to be one, or to get away with claiming to be one! It is said that those who live easy lives are forward-charging their time in heaven - for every earthly pleasure, you lose a score of the unearthly, is I believe the saying. No, they do not live uneasy lives. Take your backwards thinking elsewhere, sir."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Homosexuals are not uplifted. That‚Äôs not how the world works. They‚Äôre god‚Äôs chosen sufferers. Everything about their lives are designed to torture them, remind them of their each and every sin. It‚Äôs like a game‚Ä¶ to god. Even if they‚Äôre actually uplifted by society, given something‚Ä¶ It's just a taunt. It‚Äôs just there to remind them how much they don‚Äôt deserve it."

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: "I don't subscribe to the theory that atheists are all believers in denial, Klaud. There are people who truly accept that they deserve things that they do not. If this weren't the case, there would be no point in us informing them, spreading any truths. Do you think God would curse US to that purposelessness?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "They are reminded of nothing. Not taunted, but gifted. It's something you must accept."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "I think god loves cursing us with purposelessness. That‚Äôs what lets him have an ego."

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: "There is nothing that 'lets' God do anything. And there is certainly no amount of importance given to us that could lessen His. What religion do you follow that doesn't follow an omnipotent being?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "I‚Äôm a Catholic too. But if you‚Äôd read the bible, you‚Äôd certainly understand that god is cruel and fallible. Blind worship isn‚Äôt any real understanding of theism. And‚Ä¶ Look at what the arcticans have done. They trapped their god in a young girl and chained it. Did that monster in the ruins look omnipotent to you? If our world was blessed with magic too, maybe we‚Äôd be able to break our chains and live in a world where god can‚Äôt curse us with homosexuality."

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: "I'm afraid that I cannot look at what the articans have done. I wouldn't know where to direct my eyes. And if the monster in the ruins is not omnipotent, then... it is not God? You can gesture to any random non-omnipotent being. You must stay on track."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "But it *is* god. Ovan, as they call it."

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: "There is no world that you could live in free from God's directives. You know that, deep down. What's left to us is to reframe our world in such a way that we see nothing from Him as a curse. That is the foundation of morality. That you project your cruelty and fallibility onto Him is a failing on your part, and a reversal of the process."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "No, it isn't. Who told you that it is? Why would you trust them?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: Voreverl glares at Violetta "Great secret, never knew objects could be thrown! My war plans have been completely overturned by this revolutionary technique! Truly, I am thrilled to see what trick you think of next."

messages.content: She mutters obscenities. ‚ÄúI‚Äôve freed us both. From here on out‚Ä¶ no one can interfere.‚Äù She looks at the sky. ‚ÄúNot even you.‚Äù

messages.content: "I don't give a shit about this... what even is this? Some kind of skin deep philosophical garbage? Technology was the real villain all along! Except no, it wasn't, it was just a tool for me! I can still throw you off this roof, how's that for interfering, huh!? Wanna test your luck that you're as sturdy as that PDA?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúI‚Äôd love to. I‚Äôd love you to have anything to provide that isn‚Äôt meaningless bullshit. But I‚Äôm not holding out hope.‚Äù She takes a deep breath.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "I don't 'provide'. I take away from others. I burn down societies, tear it apart at the seams, and leave nothing left! You sure aren't giving me anything valuable here. Is that gonna change, or do you really want to see the power of Voreverl Leocot firsthand?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "I could start with the 'amazing endgame twist' you were probably going to get eventually. Hope you're not too weak to handle it." She looks to the side, annoyed.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Sure, go ahead, dazzle me with your all-seeing eye of time-wasting. I've got nothing better to do while my minion finishes their job. Might as well demonstrate my indomitable will to the masses who don't know their place."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: She stares ahead at nothing in particular. "None of it's real, Jane. It's all a farce."

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Voreverl's hands tighten into fists "The only farce here is your understanding of who you're talking to! ...Ugh, whatever! I know Arctica is a simulation or something, okay!? That was like months ago! ...In your time, at least."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "No. This." She gestures around. "They made us. Something like that. Big whoop." Violetta shrugs. "It's not like it actually matters to anyone."

author.name: scipe

messages.content:
Voreverl stares at Violetta, taking in the words. Something almost comes out of her mouth several times, but instead she just looks around her, taking in the view. Eventually, it's too much to bear, and the floodgates open. "Gw...

GWEHEHEHEHEHEHEHEHEHEH! GWEHAHAHAH! GWEHHHHAAHAHAAAAA!" She lowers herself onto the rooftop and begins holding her stomach, kicking her legs, and quite literally rolling around laughing. "I am *such* a dumbass!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Yeah."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: She calms down a bit, and just lays still, arms out, staring at the sky, grinning ear to ear. "Ever since... Avdol told me where I came from. I was actually *worried* about not being real! Gwehah! Imagine that! Voreverl Leocot turning out to the least real person in the world! It's ridiculous! But now... the playing field's been evened out! ...I would have closed the gap anyway, of course."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Voreverl Leocot isn't real, obviously. But congratulations on whatever epiphany you think you had. I tried to convince myself it meant something for a bit, but even if it's true, it means nothing. My life and my actions are still things I have to live with, and so are yours." She stares down at you. "I don't really care about the project. Not directly. I cared about John Leiblich."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "That makes one of us. What, you Jane's secret twin? That another one of your big bombshells that mean nothing? Can't imagine what business you'd have with that douche, aside from like-minds attracting one another."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "I thought he might know something. ...About her. About me. And about what's been happening more generally, I guess. But the man was impenetrable, and then he died. I figured it out, though. I should have noticed the key earlier. Obviously the thing that spawned you would also lie about his name." She smirks, and kicks you in the side.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Ow! Fuck off!" She stumbles to her feet "Voreverl Leocot *is* my... Ugh, who cares. I'll dispose of you after this, anyway. As I will with all of those who disrespect my authority. I'm not interested in the history of that foolish human waste, so it looks like we're done here."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "You should be proud. He was just as garbage as you, just as much of a coward. ...But he actually managed to kill his dad, so I guess you're still coming up short."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Voreverl Leocot does not have a father in any real sense. John Leiblich may have provided the seed for this body, but it is not even my original form. I simply stole his daughter's life away, that's all there is to it. He has no more relation to me than the factory workers who made my villainous attire."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Not really. You can never escape what made you, raised you. I don't care about your sci-fi origin story, Jane. I never knew a fuckin' infant. That's not the girl I knew or the girl I hated. It's your family that ruined my life, you included. That ruined the life of an entire lineage. Isn't that funny? It is, isn't it? Maybe you should do that obnoxious cringeworthy laugh about it."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: She cocks her head to the side "It's... nice to know my presence has enough sheer potent evil energy to ruin your life, but... Uh, I mean... I can't find it funny if I don't know what you're talking about. Was there some scheme I forgot I played on you?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
"Of course you did. You took her from me. And then your father did. And none of that would ever have happened if it wasn't for everything else... if it wasn't for an absurd coincidence. The butterfly flapping its wings on the other side of the world. If your grandfather hadn't been a lunatic, a shitty one-dimensional fuckin' psychopath that set off events that would lead to a medical practitioner similarly losing his mind and abandoning his progeny to poverty." She picks up the box from earlier. "But I guess I should thank you. Now I know what I'm supposed to do. It shouldn't really be me here. But since it is, there's only really one ending."
She slides it in your direction with considerable effort. "Brought you a gift."

It topples over onto the ground still a reasonable distance from you, spilling its contents with a loud clattering. This thing is full of a somewhat obscene amount of close range combat weapons. There's daggers, a full on sword, a metal bat... almost anything you could think of. It's impressive this all could be acquired, and also how efficiently it was packed in there.

"I'm gonna kill you. Okay? Do your best to stop me."

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Voreverl's eyes widen. She doesn't hesitate this time. No clever comebacks or stuttering surprise. She knows what she has to do.

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Voreverl runs into the door, which is locked. This is confusing for multiple reasons.

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "...Gweh... heh... good! Now you can't run away like a coward! Just... making sure we have a real cage match on our hands here!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúSure.‚Äù Her fists glint in the setting sunlight. ‚ÄúI still can‚Äôt bring myself to say her name. I don‚Äôt deserve it, Jane. See, I‚Äôm kind of a fucking monster. So seeing you play around like this‚Ä¶ it‚Äôs a little irritating. Like appropriating someone‚Äôs culture.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "...That so? 'Cause I'm thinking it over, Vi, and you know what? You've got a pretty bona fide genuine heroic origin story on your hands. Revenge against the evil lineage that rules the land, oppressing your family. Yes... yes! You're so much better than that pirate, or that... girl, the blondie... whatever her face." She approaches the pile of weapons and searches for a shortsword "But guess what, champ? The hero *always* loses. Darth Vader cuts off Luke's hand and throws him down a pit! I'll steal your life like I stole your childhood friend's most valuable possession! What a fitting end! You should be grateful I put so much thought into your execution."

Voreverl is now.  closer.

messages.content: She knocks the blade away with her fist. It‚Äôs unconventional, and does leave that hand bleeding even as she tried to center it on the brass knuckles. ‚ÄúHrr‚Ä¶ I wasn‚Äôt a bully, you fuck. I was a realist, and I only REALLY antagonized you, and I only did it because you deserve it. If you‚Äôre too much of a pansy to handle people hating you, maybe you should stop trying to make that happen, hm? But it‚Äôs fine. I‚Äôm used to being secondary in priority. Every fucking time.‚Äù She accentuates ‚Äòfucking‚Äô with a literal gut punch. using her other hand. It doesn‚Äôt draw blood, but it almost certainly bruises.

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Gwgh... Hatred isn't my goal, just a side effect of fear. People fear what they don't understand, so I bet you're terrified of your place! Tell you what, let me make the pecking order clear here. You're not my first priority, true, but you're hardly my second. Even top ten would be a stretch! So, please, don't flatter yourself!" A third stab has hit Violetta's general direction.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
This connects. It penetrates her shirt and continues onward to create a sizable wound in her abdomen. It‚Äôs shallow, but the kind of thing that will cause serious problems if not treated. It knocks the air out of her, but she refocuses her vision quickly.

She uppercuts you in the jaw. ‚ÄúMaybe this‚Äôll shut you up?‚Äù It miraculously doesn‚Äôt actually prevent you from speaking. It is, however, excruciating. She kicks you away, and with you, the blade.

‚ÄúSecond is‚Ä¶ it‚Äôs a figure of speech, you fucking *(wheeze)* moron. I mean not first. I‚Äôm barely second for anyone either, yeah. You don‚Äôt have a list that goes that far, anyway. It‚Äôs just yourself at one, right?‚Äù She spits on the ground. ‚ÄúI never know what she saw in you. I-I only ever pitied you! Nothing else. But she‚Ä¶ ohhh, she wouldn‚Äôt *ever*‚Ä¶ Comes with being immature, I guess! It‚Äôs a sort of personality that appeals to a child. *(cough)* You‚Äôve done a great job staying the exact! Fucking! Same! Right down to your first instinct being to run away, too! Hahaha!‚Äù She sidesteps around Voreverl. ‚Äú‚Ä¶Only pitied at first, I guess. Obviously things have changed.‚Äù

messages.content: "The iconography of crippling babies is facetiously grim.
